      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "@prusnak It does, against a permanent stay in the mempool, if we rather not accept the tx to the mempool, we would be giving the user a second chance to transact with a higher fee.\r\n\r\nAdding an `nSequence` bit with the meaning of \"if the lock time has passed long since, the transaction shouldn't be considered standard and not relayed\" would also equally work. (This sounds worse to me, since its more complex and can be used as an attack vector against 0-conf)",
